John Dawson Winter III (born February 23, 1944) Ã¢â‚¬â€ known as Johnny Winter Ã¢â‚¬â€ is an American blues guitarist, singer, and producer. Best known for his high-energy blues-rock albums and live performances in the late 1960s and '70s, Winter also produced three Grammy Award-winning albums for blues legend Muddy Waters. Since his time with Waters, Winter has recorded several Grammy-nominated blues albums and continues to tour extensively.
